      "message": "I think capitalizing static functions can cause confusion with class names. For example does \"auto x \u003d X();\" construct an object of type X, or does X() return some other type? When using \"auto\" I think we should be able to tell from the right-hand-side what the type will be, or at least be able to tell when it does *not* represent the type.\n\nAlso note that methods can become static or non-static based on minor design changes, and I don\u0027t think this needs reflecting in the name. If it\u0027s critical to know that a static method is being called, use \"Type::method()\".\n\nAnyway, no biggie.",
